    "user_reviews": [
      {
        "title": "Worth the config friction",
        "text": "If you are considering this card you probably know what you're after: VRAM for large inference models. While this isn't set-it-and-forget-it CUDA easily to get configured, I got it up and running on OpenVino via Llama.cpp (Ubuntu LTS, Intel Ultra9/Gmktec minipc) in 15 minutes with the help of regular ChatGPT and am enjoying 45-55tps on qwen 3.6-35b/q4/Fp8 kv. Don't believe the horror stories online. I am buying another 3 before the prices go up on all things VRAM",
        "user_name": "James",
        "source": "bhphotovideo.com",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "a week ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK1dnWVxBg_JNlHFd4onOhGYDguOz0FbD7EIViTmO38nfG5CabFtdWYAyIsG4ItT5NfLbg=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc"
      },
      {
        "title": "Don't blame the device for your own failure",
        "text": "I spent an entire weekend using this GPU with llama.cpp and vLLM, and I've been able to use models such as qwen3-coder-30b and devstral-small-2-24b.\n\nSince it's a brand new card, support is sparse and you'll have to make sure you're using current guides to get it going. I'm currently using Intel's docker container for vLLM with XPU support.",
        "user_name": "Jesse",
        "source": "bhphotovideo.com",
        "rating": 4,
        "date": "2 months ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK0NGsCm1Lvom_HlFW4HEVFg9P1DHjR56KOLkqw05UYo2M8SGEKiK6V--ER1njk51iFJVA=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc"
      },
      {
        "title": "Great card for AI work!",
        "text": "DO NOT USE REGULAR VERSION OF COMFY UI. Use ComfyUI through intel AI Playground. That version uses python 3.12 and has all the good intel PyTorch files. Regular ComfyUI will throw nVidia errors even though you are not running an nVidia card (its almost as though nVida is trying to stop people from using intel cards... WEIRD). This card is definitely not as plug and play friendly as nVidia or AMD. But its so much cheaper that its worth it. The intel software has improved so much over the last year it's crazy. Gemini told me that I should \"use the latest version of ComfyUI with my B70\", which was a total lie.\n\nThe thermal management and fan speed logic on the card is perfect. The intel software that manages it is very good now (better than AMD). There will definitely be some intel specific things you will have to learn regarding AI workloads but it's worth it in my opinion.\n\nIf your are not tech savvy and don't know how to tinker with things then definitely don't buy this card. nVidia and AMD are gonna have to lower their prices now, which is great for everyone :)",
        "user_name": "Elliott",
